casebody.data:
M. C. Davis, plaintiff in error, vs. Thomas W. Sims, administrator, defendant in error. L. L. Middlebrooks, for plaintiff in error. E. Womaoic, for defendant.

Where the clerk’s certificate to the bill of exceptions is not signed, but has simply the seal of the court thereto attached, the writ of error will be dismissed. (R.)

Bill of exceptions. Certificate. Seal. Practice in the Supreme Court. January Term, 1875.

The above head-note explains itself.
